[[!meta date="Sun, 22 Mar 2015 01:02:03 +0000"]]
[[!meta title="Numerous security holes in Tails 1.3"]]
[[!pagetemplate template="news.tmpl"]]

[[!tag security/fixed]]

Several security holes that affect Tails 1.3 are now fixed in
Tails 1.3.1.

We **strongly** encourage you to [[upgrade to
Tails 1.3.1|news/version_1.3.1]] as soon as possible.

Details
=======

 - Tor Browser: [[!mfsa 2015-28]], [[!mfsa 2015-29]]
 - Linux: [[!cve CVE-2015-1465]], [[!cve CVE-2015-1420]] and [[!cve CVE-2015-1593]]
 - OpenSSL: [[!debsa2015 3197]]
 - file and libmagic: [[!debsa2015 3196]]
 - libxfont: [[!debsa2015 3194]]
 - tcpdump: [[!debsa2015 3193]]
 - libgnutls26: [[!debsa2015 3191]]
 - libav: [[!debsa2015 3189]]
 - FreeType 2: [[!debsa2015 3188]]
 - ICU: [[!debsa2015 3187]]
 - NSS: [[!debsa2015 3186]]
 - libgcrypt11: [[!debsa2015 3185]]
 - GnuPG: [[!debsa2015 3184]]
 - libssh2: [[!debsa2015 3182]]
 - libarchive and bsdtar: [[!debsa2015 3180]]
 - libgtk2-perl: [[!debsa2015 3173]]
 - CUPS: [[!debsa2015 3172]]
